 necessary.<br><br>In duels, however, a good SK shouldn't have too much trouble killing a good Pally, depending on equipment. An SK with epic vs. a Pally with epic is no comparrision, the SK should win. (SK epic is a pretty substantial lifetap) If an SK has a Circlet of Shadow and a pally doesn't have any perma see-invis item, the Pally won't be able to keep the SK targetted long enough to do any damage. Add our pet, our debuffs, our taps, shadowstep, and we should be able to take down most paladins. The key, however, is to counteract their healing and LoH. Burning a HT at the wrong moment will likely result in the SK dying.<br><br>All in all, though, there are so many variables that would affect the duel that it'd be almost impossible to gauge. It really could go either way, in most circumstances.<br><br>In groups, I think SKs are generally more useful. We do decent damage, we can pull very well (better than monks in some cases, with our invis capability and/or a CoS, and using snares to split), we can snare, we can dot, we can out taunt/aggro any class in the game, we can keep ourselves healed fairly well in a pinch (taps), and we have a pet that can add a nice sum of damage and help interrupt casting mobs. Our spells tend to be more offensive than the Paladins, so I think in most situations an SK will out damage a Paladin due to the spells and pet (if used). Ultimately, though, it all comes down to what specific capability the group needs.<br><br>Just my opinions.<br><br>Best Regards,<br>Alaryas Ix`Stynia<br>55 Revenant (SK)<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF8DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ufailbhe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Failbhe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire<br><img s