includes lifetaps, and stuns. Healing yourself will never be resisted. <br><br>Keeping aggro is an entirely different beast. Both can outtaunt a Warrior. Heck, I as a Cleric using the right spells can outtaunt Paladins and SK's and Warriors. Does that mean I should? Of course not.<br><br>Look at your class, your strengths and weaknesses and play to your ability.  Paladins and SK's have very different roles. I'd like to see a SK stop a CHing mob as well, or a Paladin split some 60+ mobs. <br><br>Melandia Haelen<br>High Priestess of Tunare<br>Crimson Watchers<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEEFDE><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ubaaklaralasdair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baaklar Alasdair</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Knight<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif></span><br>  Posts: 152<br> <font color=#006400>(9/17/01 3:50:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=819.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Different uses.</span><hr size=1> *sigh*<br><br>I can't help but respond to this.<br><br>High enough MR, and the spells don't matter a whole lot, save Harm Touch and Lay Hands.  <br><br>ShadowKnights have some spell advantages, but I'd believe these to be offset by the Paladin's ability to heal himself, casting time and delay being the key.<br><br>The worst part for a Paladin vs. ShadowKnight battle, would be class, at least for the SK.  If the ShadowKnight is an Ogre, bet money on the Ogre.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Any other class better have high-enough MR to prevent from being stunned for the duration.<br><br>Last thing to consider is Lay Hands.  It heals for 1900 hp.  At level 53, I can buff myself to 2500 hp.  Add the 1900 to it, and that's 4400hp that an SK has to take out, before his 2500 drops to 0.  Very tough for any class to compete with that in a duelling situation, save a Warrior.<br><br>All equipment and levels being equal, it really comes down to the player himself winning the duel.  <br><br>As for grouping, it's not a fair comparison.  Paladins and ShadowKnights have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> very</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> different roles in a group, regardless of the group's makeup.<br><br>ShadowKnights can pull, Paladins can't.<br><br>Wait... rephrasing...  ShadowKnights can pull effectively, Paladins can pull trains effectively (anyone that's hunted with me knows this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br><br>Paladins can save the life of the evaccer or the enchanter or the cleric faster than any class can.  ShadowKnight's can't.<br><br>One of the nicest things about ShadowKnights in a group, is that they can snare, saving the mana of the other classes if need be.  Paladins can root if necessary (actually, don't remember if SKs can root or not).<br><br>Mez breaking - a good Paladin beats all.  ShadowKnights can do it rather well if they can get a DoT to stick, just not as well as a Paladin.<br><br>Soloing - even at higher levels, SKs can solo better, simply because they can FD and avoid an exp loss.  Paladins can avoid it, but it depends on the level and MR of the mob because of the resists.<br><br>Just my one copper... <p><img src=http://baaklar.homestead.com/files/Signatures/BaaklarSig.jpg><BR><BR>